OL,3,C'Education is everything': Asylum
OL,4,Cseekers desperate for a chance to learn
OL,6,F"It was a hard and difficult journey,"
OL,7,Fshe said. "We used to live in the
OL,8,FJungle (in Calais) in the cold, living
OL,9,Fin small tents and not having enough
OL,10,Ffood, or coats or help.
OL,12,F"It was not safe there, it was already
OL,13,Fdifficult. I didn't have any choice,
OL,14,Fto go and risk my life or to stay in
OL,15,FSomalia."
OL,17,FAlmost fluent in English, Siham taught
OL,18,Fherself by watching British and
OL,19,FAmerican films online. She spends her
OL,20,Ftime at the library and volunteering.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
