OL,3,C'Education is everything': Asylum
OL,4,Cseekers desperate for a chance to learn
OL,6,FHe showed us photographs of his
OL,7,Fchildhood in Yemen. In one image, he
OL,8,Fis at his primary school end of year
OL,9,Fcelebration, proudly holding a
OL,10,Fcertificate of achievement.
OL,12,F"I was one of the top students in the
OL,13,Fclass," he recalled. "It was really
OL,14,Fdifficult to leave my friends, my
OL,15,Fgrandparents. It's been ten years
OL,16,Fsince I last saw them."
OL,18,FMotaz is one of the 4.8 million people
OL,19,Fdisplaced by the decade-long conflict
OL,20,Fin Yemen, one of the poorest countries
OL,21,Fin the world.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
