OL,3,C'Education is everything': Asylum
OL,4,Cseekers desperate for a chance to learn
OL,6,FIt comes amid the backdrop social
OL,7,Funrest around the use of hotels to
OL,8,Fhouse asylum seekers, something that
OL,9,Fthe government has committed to ending
OL,10,Fby 2029.
OL,12,FBut some charities argue the asylum
OL,13,Fsystem needs to be transformed and
OL,14,F"lacks humanity".
OL,16,FLaura Cooper is an asylum hotel
OL,17,Fsupport worker for the Refugee Council
OL,18,Fand has spent years working with
OL,19,Fpeople living in Home Office hotels
OL,20,Facross Yorkshire.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/18
